It’s understood the pair approached the farmer asking for water and then pulled out a gun and shot him in the upper body. JOHANNESBURG - Two suspects have been arrested for the murder of a farmer in the Fochville area on the West Rand. It’s understood the pair approached the farmer asking for water and then pulled out a gun and shot him in the upper body. The motive of the murder is not known. Police say neighbours in the community confronted the suspects and handed them to police today. Spokesperson Lungelo Dlamini said: “The suspects will be facing a charge of murder and attempted murder when they appear in court within 48 hours. The local community was alerted, they confronted the suspects before handing them to the police. We will be investigating the motive for the killing.”